cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a state space representation of dynamical systems with random modes switching, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of a linear minimum mean squared error (LMMSE) filter, which is a common technique in machine learning and signal processing (cs.LG). The application of the approach to target tracking in clutter involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the use of a feedback control system and state estimator is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
